oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Gay Street
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Thompson Brothers
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Gay Street near Clinch Avenue, Knoxville, TN. 1931. McCloud's Lunches, Candy, Soda with Roi-Tan and Hava-Tampa Cigar signs. Weaver's "A Good Place to Eat" with Signs business above it. B.C.Ogle Law Offices over Martha Washington Candies, Nut Shop, Pig 'n Whistle Tabe's Orange. At right: Fouche Block Building with J.B. & W.G. Brownlow Real Estate, Lunch Room, and United Cigar Stores Co. Cars parked on street.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Business enterprises; Automobiles;
